---
const items = [
  {
    q: "I can just write a SKILL.md by hand.",
    a: "You can — and Skillmaker won't stop you (hand-edits are legal, drift is displayed, not punished). The studio earns its keep the first time a skill misbehaves and you need to know what changed, what was tested, and what was approved.",
  },
  {
    q: "Is this only for Claude?",
    a: "Bundles target any ACP-drivable agent. claude-code and codex are both full eval peers today — one skill, measured per provider, never pooled together. Publishing to a Codex-format marketplace manifest is still best-effort (no published spec to conform to yet); the git-directory and Claude-marketplace targets are on solid ground.",
  },
  {
    q: "We already have a repo full of skills. Do we have to restructure it?",
    a: "No. skillmaker adopt wraps every existing SKILL.md as a bundle in place — no files move, your layout stays yours. It's been QA'd against real public skills repos with very different structures (59/60 and 39/39 adopted). Evidence accrues from there: add fixtures to the skills you actually depend on first.",
  },
  {
    q: "Where does my data live?",
    a: "In your repo. Files plus a git-tracked JSONL journal. SQLite is a throwaway index. No server, no account.",
  },
];
---

<section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 py-16 sm:py-20">
  <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-ink">Questions</h2>
  <dl class="mt-8 divide-y divide-border border-y border-border">
    {
      items.map((item) => (
        <div class="py-6">
          <dt class="text-base font-semibold text-ink">{item.q}</dt>
          <dd class="mt-2 text-sm leading-relaxed text-ink-dim">{item.a}</dd>
        </div>
      ))
    }
  </dl>
</section>
